<%- include("partials/header.ejs") %>
<%#
<section id="0">
    <div class="container my-4">
        <div class="p-5 text-center bg-body-tertiary rounded-3">
            <div class="userProfilePic text-left">
                <img src="images/ndivo_animation_lana.jpg" class="mx-2 card-img-top rounded-circle d-inline-flex float-start" alt="..." style="text-align: left;">
                <h5 class="text-body-emphasis mb-2 px-5" style="text-align: left;">@dennis</h5>
            </div>
          <h3 class="text-body-emphasis pb-3 fs-4">Getting Started with Game Development: A Beginner's Guide</h3>
          <p class="col-lg-12 mx-auto fs-8 text-muted" style="text-align: justify;">
            1. Choose a Game Engine<br>
            The first step in game development is choosing a game engine. Game engines provide the tools and 
            frameworks necessary to build and deploy games across different platforms. Popular game engines 
            include Unity, Unreal Engine, and Godot. Take some time to explore different engines and choose 
            the one that best fits your needs and skill level.<br>

            2. Learn the Basics of Programming<br>
            While you don't need to be a programming expert to start making games, having a basic understanding 
            of programming concepts will be incredibly helpful. Start by learning a programming language 
            commonly used in game development, such as C#, JavaScript, or Python. There are plenty of online 
            resources and tutorials available to help you get started.<br>

            3. Experiment with Game Design<br>
            Game design is the process of creating the rules, mechanics, and overall structure of a game. 
            Experiment with different game ideas and mechanics to find what resonates with you. Consider 
            creating simple prototypes or mock-ups to test out your ideas and see how they feel in practice.<br>

            4. Create Art and Assets<br>
            Visuals play a crucial role in game development, helping to set the tone and atmosphere of your 
            game. Whether you're an artist or not, there are plenty of resources available for creating game 
            art and assets. Experiment with pixel art, 3D modeling, or even hand-drawn sketches to bring your 
            game to life.
          </p>
          <img src="images/flying-man-cyberpunk-portrait.jpg" class="card-img-top postIMG" alt="...">
          <div class="gap-2">
            <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm px-4 rounded-pill" type="button">
              Edit
            </button>
            <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm px-4 rounded-pill" type="button">
                Delete
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
</section>
%>

<% if(locals.posts) {%>
<% for(var i = 0; i < posts.length; i++) {%>
<section id="<%= posts[i].id %>">
    <div class="container my-4">
        <div class="p-5 text-center bg-body-tertiary rounded-3">
            <div class="userProfilePic text-left">
                <img src="images/<%= posts[i].profileImage %>" class="mx-2 card-img-top rounded-circle d-inline-flex float-start" alt="..." style="text-align: left;">
                <h5 class="text-body-emphasis mb-2 px-5" style="text-align: left;"><%= posts[i].name %></h5>
            </div>
          <h3 class="text-body-emphasis pb-3 fs-4"><%= posts[i].postTitle %></h3>
          <p class="col-lg-12 mx-auto fs-8 text-muted" style="text-align: justify;">
            <%= posts[i].postDesc %>
          </p>
          <img src="images/<%= posts[i].postImage %>" class="card-img-top postIMG" alt="...">
          <div class="gap-2">
            <form method="post" action="/get_Post_Edit" style="display: inline;">
              <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm px-4 rounded-pill editButton" type="submit" name="currentId" value = "<%= posts[i].id %>">
                Edit
              </button>
            </form>
            <form method="post" action="/delete_post" style="display: inline;">
              <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm px-4 rounded-pill" type="submit" name="currentId" value = "<%= posts[i].id %>">
                Delete
            </button>
            </form>
            
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
</section>
<% }}%>

<%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>